commitResults.messageTitle: Added reserve and return functions, imported Ui into InstrumentList in order to get user input as part of reserve and return functions Edited COMMANDLIST in Ui to reflect new functions
Updated docs/AboutUs.md to include my name (Kashfy), changed link in portfolio to my github username (kashfyzul)
Removed confirmation option for Reserve and Return
Introduced feature to include return date when reserving an instrument Added "dueBy" attribute to Instrument class Introduced parser method and exception for reserving of instrument
Added "addExistingInstrument()" in InstrumentList. Method is called in Storage when reading from txt file Allows app to recognise previously listed instruments as rented

Edited instrument constructors to take in LocalDate "dueBy" arguments for rented instruments instead of boolean "isRented" output txt file now reflects the dueBy or return date of reserved instruments
Added Extend command, allows user to edit the return date of a reserved instrument
Added "Extend", allows user to change the "rentedTo" date of an instrument
Remaining stocks for each instrument is reflected when user lists all available instruments
Upon startup of app, instruments that are low in quantity are printed to the console to notify the user
Organised the stocklist in printStockList to a table format, showing total qty and rented qty of instruments

User is able to check stocks, and is notified of depleting stocks
